The following are major news items in leading Indian
newspapers today: The Hindustan Times -- Tamil Nadu police, who have
been searching the residence of former chief minister Jayalalitha since
her arrest on a corruption charge on Friday, have seized multi-crore
worth of gold, silver, jewelry and other properties. The Times of India
-- The Supreme Court Monday asked the government to initiate a pilot
project to determine whether comparatively cheaper propane fuel is
eco-friendly. The Statesman -- Insurance employees observed a
nation-wide strike Monday in protest against the proposed privatization
of the insurance sector. The Economic Times -- The National Stock
Exchange of India Monday declared three of its members as defaulters
following their failure to meet financial obligations.
